Prologue
“Please!” Queen Elwin pleaded, “Don’t send her away! She’s just a child!” The Ice King sat on his throne, looking down at his wife, with the royal advisor standing nearby. The queen had given birth to a girl. Just thinking about it, the Ice King couldn’t help but furrow his brow.
The infant looked very much like her mother: pale blue eyes, snow-white hair, with a few strands of blue hair. The Ice King thought having a daughter would make him look weak. After all, before this, he had only had a son.
“You only have two choices: either kill this child or leave her in the wilderness. Elwin, this is your punishment.” He spat out her name with hatred, as if it were poison. He always did this.
The Frostland Kingdom was not always a kingdom. It once split into two parts, north and south. The north established a non-magical kingdom, while the south was a kingdom full of magical powers. Due to the greed of the north, the two kingdoms waged endless wars until the south proposed a truce.
The Southern Kingdom was already in despair, and the royal family was willing to do anything to stop the bloody conflict. They proposed marrying the only princess to the North, making her queen of the North and giving birth to a son who would be the future king. After that, the South would merge with the North to establish a unified kingdom. The North accepted this proposal, and Princess Elwin was married to Prince Akurl.
"Please, my king, for the safety of my child, you can do anything to me—imprison me, exile me, even kill me," Queen Elwin pleaded, hugging her child tightly in her arms.
The Ice King looked down at the queen, his eyes filled with hatred. Perhaps, just perhaps, he would have a bit of mercy for her. After all, this woman had accompanied him for 22 years, cared for him during his most desperate times, and bore him children.
"Well. The child can stay in the palace," said the Ice King, and upon hearing this, Queen Elwin breathed a sigh of relief. "But," he added, "you will be executed."
The royal advisor and Queen Elwin both showed terrified expressions. She slowly lowered her head, looking at the floor. "As you command, my king," she bowed.
The Ice King ordered the royal advisor to take the queen's daughter to an empty room belonging to Elwin. After that, he ordered the guards to take Elwin to the execution ground where all citizens could see.
As the guards led her to the execution ground, the citizens saw their only queen—also the kindest queen—about to be executed, and they felt very angry. Some cried, some shouted and tried to attack the guards, and others wondered why such a thing was happening; but they all had the same question.
"Let her go!"
"Why are they treating her like this?"
As Elwin approached the wooden stake, the most terrifying person in the kingdom appeared. He was the executioner for the fire刑. The former queen Elwin would be burned alive. No one should be subjected to fire刑, even criminals. In the Frostland Kingdom, fire刑 was the most cruel punishment.
Elwin was tied to the wooden post, and the king began to tell how the queen had betrayed them all. The people of the Frostland Kingdom refused to believe, and would never accept the king's words. Then, the executioner lit the wooden post, and a single tear rolled down the face of the former queen.
"Carly, live on!" The life of Queen Elwin came to an end.
The hall was completely silent
In the southern wing of this cold palace, the endless "tick-tick" sound came from the leftmost room. Former servants were always curious about what was inside the room, yet too fearful to approach. The maids moved around the hall, whispering and spreading all sorts of rumors. Some believed that the late queen Elwin lived in this room, waiting to be released.
They were completely wrong. Avery thought as she walked toward the southern wing, the servants walked along the walls, whispering to each other. They had no idea what was inside.
Of course, there are also many rumors about her, because she is the only one allowed to enter the room.
She knocked on the door. "Miss Carly, are you in there?" Avery whispered to this complex door, decorated with snowflakes and crowns, symbols of the royal family.
She didn't know if she would really be let in this time, which was different from before. I still have the bruises from last time. Avery recalled this incident and couldn't help but laugh. At that time, Carly threw a book at him, but when she saw who it was, she immediately apologized.
A light sound came from the room, as if saying she couldn't go anywhere, she was just there.
"May I come in?" Avery asked, remembering the consequences of entering uninvited last time.
A light sound came again from the room. It seemed to be saying "Come in." Avery felt a chill, unsure whether it was from the cold or from that voice. Although she had been there for many years, hearing the sound from the room made her feel a bit strange.
"I'm coming in," Avery said, slowly opening the door. From a normal person's perspective, the scene in the room was quite unusual, but that was also expected. The room was filled with paper. Books were scattered on the floor, the table was broken, and there were many ice sculptures in the room. There were no windows, and there was almost no light. This room was also colder than other parts of the palace (which explained a lot). The room looked as if it had been attacked by a blizzard, with everything in disarray.
The girl in the room was curled up in bed, wrapped in blankets, reading a notebook. A small lantern lit up the room.
"Which notebook are you reading?" Avery asked as she sat by Carly's bed.
